on damage was also reduced because of his lowered STR in all cases.<br><br>Conclusion: Although the SPECS on the poison itself (when doing a SHIFT+i) tells of a much higher STR debuff, this is not the case. Overall, it is a decent poison IF you can kill your opponent before the 1 minute expiry time wears off. <br>----------------------------------------------<br>Disease Poison<br>(we could not test out the HEALING disabilities this poison might cause, since we had no healer around)<br><br>Lesser Infectious (level 16)<br>- 7 Strength<br>Slowed his running speed by approximately 15% <br>The “snare” did NOT break, if he was hit after he was poisoned.<br><br>Infectious Serum (level 26)<br>-10 Strength <br>Slowed his running speed by approximately 25%<br>The “snare” did NOT break, if he was hit after he was poisoned.<br><br>Conclusion: A decent way to slow down your opponent when he is trying to get away.<br>----------------------------------------------<br>Snare Poisons<br><br>Major Imbalance Poison (level 13)<br>Slowed his running speed by approximately 35-40%.<br><br>Greater Imbalance Poison (level 18 )<br>Slowed his running speed by approximately 35-40%. (same as the Major)<br><br>Minor Crippling Poison (level 23)<br>Slowed his running speed by approximately 35-40%. (same as above 2)<br><br>Lesser Crippling Poison (level 27)<br>Slowed his running speed by approximately 35-40%. (same as above 3)<br><br>Notes: His running speed was the SAME when each of the 4 snares was used. His speed was almost identical as my speed when running, while stealthed.<br>If there is a DOT (spell or poison) on him, the Snare poison will BREAK.<br>If you engage and hit the opponent, the Snare poison will BREAK.<br>If there is a bleed (from weapon or spell) on him, the Snare poison will BREAK!<br><br>Conclusion: AMAZING slowing poison, unfortunately any kind of after effect (be it mele or spell) will break the snare and return full movement to the enemy.<br>------------------------------------------------<br>In conclusion, I am rather disappointed by the change in the Enervating poisons. The snare line is good, but I can’t viably see myself using it in RvR, because of the speed slow effect, wearing off once mele is engaged. The DoT is still the same as it always was, and I was quite pleased with the effects of the Disease poison—which I will continue to use.<br><br>Just wanted to thank Druis, for his help in setting this up, and calling me all the way from Idaho (Ontario boy here). Cudos to ya man! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->      Hope to see ya our there sometime!<br><br>Druis' post and anything I might have missed, can be found here:<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=24036093&replies=2">vnboards.ign.com/message....&replies=2</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Jaax.<br> <p><img src="http://www.flavonsen.com/images/jaax-face.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujaaxtherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jaax the Rogue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/13/02 8:27:48 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usabbyfkb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sabbyFKB</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/02 12:04:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2144.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New poison TESTS. Interesting results...</span><hr size=1> &quot;Minor Enervating Poison (level 22)<br>-31 Strength<br>-31 Constitution (which dropped 85 of his Hit points)&quot;<br><br><br